        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">DIY vs. Professional Move-Out Cleaning</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Can you clean your rental yourself? Absolutely. But here's the honest truth about what that involves:
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Time required:</strong> 8-15 hours depending on size and condition, after you've already exhausted yourself packing and moving.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Supplies needed:</strong> All-purpose cleaner, degreaser, glass cleaner, bathroom cleaner, floor cleaner, scrub brushes, microfiber cloths, mop, vacuum (one that actually works well), step stool for high areas, and specialty products for hard water and grout.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Knowledge required:</strong> Understanding exactly what property managers inspect and their standards for "clean."
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Risk:</strong> Missing items that result in charges exceeding what professional cleaning would have cost.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Why Professional Makes Sense</h3>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          A professional move-out clean from The Valley Clean Team typically costs $199-400 for Huntsville-area properties, depending on size. For that investment, you get:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
          <li>A team that knows exactly what property managers check</li>
          <li>Commercial-grade products that actually remove stubborn buildup</li>
          <li>Completion in 2-4 hours while you handle other moving tasks</li>
          <li>An itemized receipt proving professional cleaning was performed</li>
          <li>Dramatically reduced risk of cleaning-related deductions</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          We're veteran-owned, carry $2 million in insurance coverage, and send the same trusted team to every job. We've done hundreds of move-out cleans in Madison County alone—we know what the local property managers expect.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Timeline for Move-Out Cleaning</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          When should you schedule your move-out clean? Here's the ideal timeline:
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>2 weeks before move-out:</strong> Start decluttering and deep cleaning areas you can complete early (inside cabinets, closets, garage).
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>1 week before:</strong> Schedule professional cleaning or block time for DIY cleaning after furniture is removed.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Day of/after furniture removal:</strong> Complete final clean or have professionals come. Everything needs to be out first—you can't properly clean around furniture.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Before key turn-in:</strong> Do a final walk-through with your phone camera. Document everything. Email photos to yourself for timestamped proof.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Protecting Yourself Legally</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Alabama law provides some protection for tenants, but you need to know your rights:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
          <li>Landlords have 35 days to return your deposit with an itemized list of any deductions</li>
          <li>Deductions must be "reasonable" and documented</li>
          <li>Normal wear and tear cannot be deducted</li>
          <li>Wrongful withholding can result in double damages in court</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The best protection? Don't give them anything to deduct. A thorough move-out clean eliminates the most common dispute items entirely.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Your Move-Out Cleaning Checklist</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Whether you clean yourself or hire professionals, here's what needs to happen:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
          <li>All appliances cleaned inside and out</li>
          <li>All cabinets and drawers wiped clean</li>
          <li>All bathroom fixtures scrubbed, grout addressed</li>
          <li>All floors vacuumed/mopped</li>
          <li>All windows, tracks, and blinds cleaned</li>
          <li>All light fixtures and ceiling fans dusted</li>
          <li>All baseboards wiped down</li>
          <li>All closets cleaned</li>
          <li>All HVAC vents dusted</li>
          <li>Garage floor swept/cleaned</li>
          <li>All nail holes filled (if required by lease)</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Bottom line:</strong> Your security deposit is your money. Don't let a property manager keep it because of cleaning issues that could have been prevented. Whether you DIY or hire professionals like us, make sure it's done right.
        </p>

        <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
